00:00:23.080 --> 00:00:24.970
&gt;&gt; Joan Weeks: I'd like to
welcome you to the African

00:00:24.970 --> 00:00:28.060
and Middle East Division
at the Library of Congress

00:00:28.060 --> 00:00:30.420
and to our noontime lecture series

00:00:30.420 --> 00:00:36.170
with today's program entitled
the Sultan's Gift, Book Diplomacy

00:00:36.170 --> 00:00:40.600 position:56%
in the Hamidian Period by Guy Burak.

00:00:40.600 --> 00:00:43.830
And it's sponsored by the Near
East section of the African

00:00:43.830 --> 00:00:45.570
and Middle East Division.

00:00:45.570 --> 00:00:48.070
I'm Joan Weeks, I'm head
of the Near East section

00:00:48.070 --> 00:00:49.930
and the Turkish specialist.

00:00:49.930 --> 00:00:54.560
And on behalf of all my colleagues
and especially Dr. Mary Jane Deeb,

00:00:54.560 --> 00:00:57.040
chief of the division, she
may join us in a little bit

00:00:57.040 --> 00:00:59.570
with some of our guests today.

00:00:59.570 --> 00:01:02.570
I'd like to extend a very
warm welcome to everyone.

00:01:02.570 --> 00:01:06.750
But before we start today's program
and introduce our speaker I'd

00:01:06.750 --> 00:01:10.820
like to give you a brief overview
of our division and its resources.

00:01:10.820 --> 00:01:13.520
I know many of you've heard
this before many times,

00:01:13.520 --> 00:01:17.350
but we also have some
visitors with us.

00:01:17.350 --> 00:01:18.650
In the hopes that you'll come back

00:01:18.650 --> 00:01:22.750
and use our beautiful reading
room for your research.

00:01:22.750 --> 00:01:27.580
This division is comprised
of three sections that build

00:01:27.580 --> 00:01:31.510
and serve the collections to
researchers from around the world.

00:01:31.510 --> 00:01:37.270
We cover 75 countries and
more than two dozen languages.

00:01:37.270 --> 00:01:43.660 position:56%
The Africa section covers all of
the countries of sub-Saharan Africa.

00:01:43.660 --> 00:01:48.720
The Hebraic section is responsible
for Judaica and Hebraica worldwide.

00:01:48.720 --> 00:01:53.000
And the Near East section covers
all of the Arab countries,

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:57.870
including North Africa, Turkey,
Turkic Central Asia, Iran,

00:01:57.870 --> 00:02:03.040
Afghanistan, the Muslims in western
China, Russia and the Balkans,

00:02:03.040 --> 00:02:06.890
and the peoples of the Caucasus.

00:02:06.890 --> 00:02:10.620
After the program we invite
you to fill in the little forms

00:02:10.620 --> 00:02:12.070
